4. Prove that you cannot access default property but can access protected property from subclass.
Code
class Parent {

    int a = 10; // default

    protected int b = 20;
}

class Child extends Parent {

    void display() {

        // System.out.println(a); // not accessible in another package

        System.out.println(b);
    }
}

class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Child c = new Child();

        c.display();
    }
}
Output
20
Explanation
default → accessible only within same package

protected → accessible in subclass using inheritance
